cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "XFMS — Xpansion Framework Model Source"
message: "If you use XFMS in academic work or product evaluation, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Wright
    given-names: Russ
    email: russ@visionairy.biz
    affiliation: Visionairy
abstract: >
  XFMS is the model-selection module of the Xpansion Framework. Given a
  user purpose, it returns a ranked shortlist of LLMs with per-pick
  rationale, aggregating evidence from eight independent third-party
  benchmark sources without trusting provider self-reported numbers.
  Score normalization, name resolution across sources, coverage-gated
  weight renormalization, and user-intent override are all documented
  in docs/methodology.md. This repository is the client library; the
  recommender engine and catalog run as a hosted service.
url: "https://github.com/VisionAIrySE/XFMS"
